  "time_ut": 1658732952,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3 \u0dbd\u0dcf\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0da2\u0db4\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dba\u0dda \u0d9a\u0dd8\u0dc2\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db8\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dba\u0dda \u0daf\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dad\u0dca \u0d87\u0dbb\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The door of agriculture in Japan is also open to Sri Lankans",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Foreign Employment Bureau of Sri Lanka states that the Japanese government has agreed to provide employment opportunities to Sri Lankan workers in the agriculture sector in addition to the jobs in the nursing and food and beverage services sectors that Japan has provided to Sri Lanka under the Special Skilled Employment Program.",
        "Accordingly, more Sri Lankan workers have been given the opportunity to be directed to jobs in the agricultural sector under the employment program with special skills.",
        "With the intervention of the Embassy of Sri Lanka in Japan and other institutions, approval has been obtained for employment opportunities in this agricultural sector, and the Embassy has played a special role in this.",
        "Jobs in the agricultural sector require professional qualifications in addition to Japanese language proficiency, and qualified individuals over the age of 17 can apply, the bureau notes.",
        "Examinations related to Merit Test 2022 July 29 and 31, August 2,3,5,7-10,19,21,23-26 and 28, September 1,2,4,6,7,9 and 11, October 11- 13, 16, 18-20 and 23 and November 8-10, 13, 15 and 16 will be conducted through computer.",
        "This exam will be held at the Australia College of Business and Technology located at Lester James Peiris Mawatha Mawatha, Colombo Five.",
        "A maximum of 150 candidates can appear for the exam per month and the exam fee is 3500 Japanese Yen or 6300.00 Sri Lanka Rupees.",
        "The information required to enter this examination can be obtained by visiting the Japanese Job Portal (SSW Japan) on the website of the Sri Lanka Foreign Employment Bureau www.slbfe.lk."
      ],
